      • preparingStateChanges

        private java.util.List<OntStateChangeBuf> preparingStateChanges(long unitConnectionTime,
                                                                java.util.List<OntStateChangeBuf> stateChanges)
                                                         throws org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException
        Method is used to check and prepare the input information, which should be aggregated.
        Parameters:
        unitConnectionTime - is the time, which describes the connection time in milliseconds between unit and bco. Inconspicuous connection states should have connection times equal the time frame of aggregation.
        stateChanges - are the state changes, which should be sorted ascending by including timestamp.
        Returns:
        the sorted list of state changes.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException - is thrown in case the verification of input information, which should be aggregated, is invalid.

      • calcTimeWeighting

        private double calcTimeWeighting(long unitConnectionTime)
        Method calculates the time weighting of a connection time. Means a value, which describes the ratio of connection time and period time. If an unit has connection the whole period the value is 1. If the unit has connection half of the period time the value is 0.5. The range is [0..1].
        Parameters:
        unitConnectionTime - is the connection time of the unit.
        Returns:
        the time weighting in the range of [0..1].
